I was watching the log live through ``tail -f log.txt``.

I opened up vim, pressed ``Shift + ;``, then pressed ``q`` and then pressed ``Enter``. The keyboard events fired accordingly. After that, I had to press Enter again (but any other key works as well) to close the dangling terminal.

issue.body:
This has been reported (and fixed) multiple times earlier https://github.com/jwilm/alacritty/issues/201, https://github.com/jwilm/alacritty/issues/915, https://github.com/jwilm/alacritty/issues/1313, https://github.com/jwilm/alacritty/issues/1342. But I'm still running into this bug when exiting fish shell.

Running Arch Linux, X11 with xf86-video-amdgpu driver, Awesome WM, and alacritty 0.2.7-1.

Can reproduce it every time with
```
alacritty -e fish -c exit
```
These work ok
```
alacritty -e bash -c exit
lxterminal -e fish -c exit
```

Output of `alacritty --print-events -e fish -c exit`:
